Messages: 16 is the minimum age that one can drop out of school in most states of the US (however, restrictions apply and vary depending on state).
16 is the number of personality types in the Myers-Briggs classification system.
16 is the number of teams that qualified for the finals of the FIFA World Cup from 1934 through 1978 (although for various reasons, only 15 competed in the 1938 and 1950 finals).
16 is the minimum age for getting an adult job in most states and provinces across the globe.
